description: Compiler errors due to incompatible pointer types in SSL functions: __gmpz_sizeinbase() receives wrong pointer type for modulus and exponent arguments. Makefile build fails with exit status 1.
Multiple functions lack explicit return type declarations, triggering -Wimplicit-int errors during compilation (lsg_p(), rsg_p(), ortgn()). Build fails at ccst2.c compilation.
CMake configuration failure: cmake_minimum_required specifies outdated CMake version (<3.5). Compatibility with old CMake versions has been removed, requiring VERSION argument update.
Type mismatch in retro-core.c: argument 3 of ipc_runner_call_get_memory_size_sync() expects different pointer type (&size). Ninja build fails during C compilation.
Type mismatch in header-py.c: tp_hash function pointer expects Py_hash_t (*)(PyObject*) but receives long int (*)(PyObject*). Python setup.py build fails during C extension compilation.
snappy function arguments mismatch: snappy_uncompressed_length(), snappy_uncompress(), and snappy_validate_compressed_buffer() receive incompatible pointer types for buffer arguments in cache.c.
Build failure during Ruby setup-rb script execution (exit status 1). Likely related to Ruby gem extensions or dependency issues.
Rust compilation errors in derive_more-impl, enum-map-derive, and hyper_util crates. Includes ELF verification warnings about debug sections and non-LFS functions.
Pointer/integer type mismatch in schedtool.c conditional expression (CHECK_RANGE_POLICY). Triggers -Wint-conversion error during compilation.
Build dependency failure: automake_1.11 package is unavailable. Required for generating build files but missing from repository.
